Here are my FAVOURITE dances from Season 5 of So You&nbsp;Think You&nbsp;Can Dance so far (in no order of preference): 

(i) Episode 2 - Melissa and Ade doing a Sonya Tayeh Jazz routine to &quot;24 Hours (The Ashton Shuffle A-Bomb Remix)&quot; by Terry Poison; 

(ii) Episode 10 - Evan and Randi doing a Mia Michaels Contemporary routine to &quot;Koop Island Blues&quot; by Koop feat. Ane Brun; 

(iii) Episode 14 - Kayla and Kupono doing a Mia Michaels Contemporary routine to &quot;Gravity&quot; by Sara Bareilles; 

(iv) Episode 14 - Brandon and Janette doing an Argentine Tango by Miriam Larici and Leonardo Barrionuevo to &quot;Libertango&quot; from Forever Tango (the original Broadway cast); 

(v) Episode 14 - Janette and Brandon doing a Wade Robson Jazz routine to &quot;Ruby Blue&quot; by Roisin Murphy. 

The Janette/Brandon Argentine Tango was AMAZING&nbsp;AMAZING&nbsp;AMAZING...so so so good. The Kayla/Kupono Mia Michaels Contemporary routine gave me chills and at one point I almost teared a little!! And Wade Robson is just such an excellent choreographer..I really like Sonya Tayeh and Mia Michaels too..

I like the dances in Season 5 more than I like any particular danceRs..unlike Season 4 where I just loved loved LOVE Joshua and Katiee (and also&nbsp;Twitch but to a less degree). So many more dances from them that I love watching over and over again than in the current season...

Sigh..so..yeah..i wish i could dance!!

It is about half an hour to the end of my last day of unemployment. 

I feel really bummed and nervous about starting work again after such a long break. I am totally not excited man. 

I didn't do some stuff which I think I should probably have done in my 3 months break. I didn't really think about trying out another industry, I didn't join some dance or language class to have something to show for my 3 months break, I didn't go into JB to see my grandma, I didn't really do anything which helped anyone...3 months just flew by so fast! It doesn't even feel like it's been that long...

Here's what I did do these 3 months: 

1. Went to HK with parents; 

2. Went for yoga classes at least once a week (except for the 2 weeks I was in Europe and the 2 weeks when I got back and was feeling tremendously lazy); 

3. Went to Europe with Baby; 

4. Attempted many times to pack my room. 

5. Went to HK with parents, big bro, sis-in-law and Sarah (my niece); 

6. Spent time playing with Sarah; 

7. Did a bunch of wedding related stuff (I am not insane ok); 

8. Finished reading 10 books; 

9. Finished watching all 10 seasons of F.R.I.E.N.D.S; 

10. Met up/hung out with my friends; 

11. Cooked dinner 4 times; 

12. Got a job. 

 So I've done my nails, packed my bag, hung out my clothes for tomorrow and laid out my accessories and make up. So I guess I'm ready for work tomorrow?

We just arrived in Budapest and our apartment is really really really awesome. It has a computer with internet and all so it's really great.&nbsp;

Quick update on the trip so far. We are safe and sound. I have been sick though and it's been frustrating because I can't eat and I keep having to go back earlier because I am so tired. I think I might still be jet lagged although I don't know why because it's been a few days. Maybe coz I'm not as young as I used to be already because I don't remember taking this long to get over jet lag.&nbsp;

Vienna was disappointing. We went at a bad time where everything was CLOSED. They really respect rest days. Shops are closed on Sundays and we very suay the last day there it was a public holiday so everything was closed too. The main tourist sites were open but no shopping for us.&nbsp;

Hoping I will start to feel better and stop ruining Baby's trip.
